<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="434" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,151,1004]" pageId="33" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,944,968]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="434" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[834,890,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="434">vulv-</emphasis>
(= fold) and the adjective postfix 
<emphasis box="[1268,1325,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="434">-idus</emphasis>
, referring to the juxta folding inward laterally in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
